<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:red">[K]</span> <a href="/scp-4255">SCP-4255</a> - Santa Claus, the Time Traveler</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>I hope some crazy government shoots me out of the sky so I can get this hell over with.</em></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Commentary:</strong> My first SCP posted. I still have a soft spot for it, and am still a bit surprised that this dorky idea about Santa Claus being a time traveling prisoner of the Foundation <em>actually worked out</em>. I mean I'm not complaining. I really want to make an image for this, but I am to lazy to do that at the moment.</p>
<p><strong>Fun Fact:</strong> The original draft had Santa get killed by the Global Occult Coalition launching a missile at him. This however, was pretty dumb.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:red">[K]</span> <a href="/scp-4157">SCP-4157</a> - WANT DOG</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Jesus is my favorite snake width too!</em></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Commentary:</strong> This was an idea I've had for a while, before dado was popular actually. When I found out about dado I was like &quot;well shit&quot;, but then I still tried to pull this off, and people like it, so I guess that's a good thing! This seriously though is one of my first ideas for an SCP I've ever had, and so this article is a lot more personal to me.</p>
<p><strong>Fun Fact:</strong> The number for this one is actually an A1B2Z26 cipher for dog, meaning D=4&#160;O=15 and G=7.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:green">[S]</span> <a href="/scp-4488">SCP-4488</a> - <span style="font-family:times new roman;"><span style="font-size:125%;">Thalassophobia</span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">With <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-trashman" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4907992); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4907992&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608430604" alt="The Trashman" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4907992)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-trashman" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4907992); return false;">The Trashman</a></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>And while you wait, why not wonder what might be out there for a change?</em></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Commentary:</strong> This was a collab piece with <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-trashman" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4907992); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4907992&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608430604" alt="The Trashman" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4907992)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-trashman" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4907992); return false;">The Trashman</a></span>, who I know in real life. The entire writing process of this basically consists of him coming up with the idea, him writing a draft, me seeing the draft and saying &quot;no that bad&quot; and then rewriting 70% of it. I added the spooky ending, and just hope that I have made his first SCP a good one.</p>
<p><strong>Fun Fact:</strong> The main idea for this according to Trashman came from the &quot;The stranger the fear the better&quot; line in the How To Write An SCP guide.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:red">[K]</span> <a href="/scp-4667">SCP-4667</a> - I Am Become Teeth</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>We have heard your cries in the teeth of our patients.</em></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Commentary:</strong> So yeah teeth. Funnily enough, this sorta started out as a SCP-089-ARC rewrite, I however decided to overhaul the entire concept and just make it about a tooth god. This is one of my favorite works I've written, surpassed on by SCP-5666. It was so fun to put together the logs and have everything come into place in the end.</p>
<p><strong>Fun Fact:</strong> Every single image in this besides the header image was found using the &quot;Random File&quot; button on Wikimedia Commons.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:orange">[E]</span> <a href="/scp-3725">SCP-3725</a> - Ironically, I don't have a Good Idea for a Title</p>
